     HEADLINES AND ANNOTATIONS

     FOR REPORT DIAGRAMS IN CENTERFOLD

     AND SECOND TO LAST PAGE:          Outpatient and Inpatient

                                          AHR is certain to require the

                                       reporting of revenue and related

                                       standard units of measure by program

                                       service.  In this example,

                                       laboratory revenue and workload

                                       measurement units are accumulated

                                       and reported by the outpatient

                                       clinic program service.

                                       Additionally, data for ten methods

                                       of payment is reported.  Comparable

                                       reports are developed for each

                                       applicable program service area.

                                          Another example of how a TMS

                                       report identifies patient service

                                       revenue and standard units of

                                       measure by program service.

