     INSIDE BACK COVER, SUBHEAD:       Tymshare and Tymshare Medical

                                       Systems: A Proven Record of

                                       Excellence

     COPY:                                 Founded in 1965, Tymshare, Inc.,

                                       is a pioneer in the remote computer

                                       services field.  The company was

                                       among the first to implement the

                                       novel concept of "timesharing", the

                                       use of a central computer by a

                                       number of geographically distant

                                       users.  The economies of this

                                       approach to computer service as well

                                       as the innovative development of

                                       user software, communications

                                       services, and many other related

                                       technological advances have

                                       propelled Tymshare to the forefront

                                       of computer service companies.  In

                                       1980, its revenues were over $200

                                       million.

                                          Among the new areas of automation

                                       pioneered by Tymshare has been the

                                       medical field through its

                                       subsidiary, Tymshare Medical




                                     -more-









     AHR BROCHURE
     page 11 



                                       Systems.  TMS is a unique blend of

                                       talent in medical administration,

                                       software development, and computer

                                       technology.  It focuses on the

                                       problems of health care facility

                                       managers in improving efficiency and

                                       containing costs by the use of

                                       automation techniques.  Today, TMS

                                       services are being used routinely in

                                  scores of hospitals throughout the

